HEADWORD: Southwester
<hw>South`west"er</hw> <pr>(?; <xex>colloq</xex>. <?/)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A storm, gale, or strong wind from the
southwest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A hat made of painted canvas, oiled cloth, or the
like, with a flap at the back, -- worn in stormy weather.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Southwesterly</ent>⟦br⟧
